# Frontend Design

## Anti-AI-Slop Rules

Never use:
- Generic fonts (Inter, Roboto, Arial, system fonts)
- Purple gradients on white backgrounds
- Cookie-cutter layouts, predictable component patterns
- Same design choices across different components

## Guidelines

- **Typography**: distinctive font pairings — display + body. Choose fonts with character.
- **Color**: cohesive palette via CSS variables. Dominant colors with sharp accents, not evenly-distributed.
- **Motion**: CSS-only where possible. One well-orchestrated page load with staggered reveals > scattered micro-interactions.
- **Composition**: asymmetry, generous negative space or controlled density. Grid-breaking where appropriate.
- **Atmosphere**: depth via gradient meshes, noise textures, geometric patterns, layered transparencies, shadows, grain.

Match implementation complexity to aesthetic vision — maximalist needs elaborate code, minimalist needs precision.
